WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.560 --> 00:00:02.320
Where is the
nearest coffee shop?

00:00:02.320 --> 00:00:04.910
Where can I get
cheap gas nearby?

00:00:04.910 --> 00:00:06.580
What time is the next bus?

00:00:06.580 --> 00:00:10.000
If your Android app knows the
user's location and context,

00:00:10.000 --> 00:00:13.080
it can offer the most
relevant help and information

00:00:13.080 --> 00:00:14.650
in the moment.

00:00:14.650 --> 00:00:16.870
Take the location
and contacts course

00:00:16.870 --> 00:00:19.060
built by Udacity
in Google to learn

00:00:19.060 --> 00:00:22.470
how to update your Android app
to detect the user's location

00:00:22.470 --> 00:00:26.070
and activity to offer the best
possible experience-- no matter

00:00:26.070 --> 00:00:28.590
where the user is, no
matter what they're doing.

00:00:28.590 --> 00:00:31.340
Learn how to use the
Fused Location Provider

00:00:31.340 --> 00:00:33.230
to get the current location.

00:00:33.230 --> 00:00:36.240
Delve into Activity
Recognition to tailor your app

00:00:36.240 --> 00:00:37.830
to what the user is doing.

00:00:37.830 --> 00:00:41.850
Learn how location services
work alongside Geofences

00:00:41.850 --> 00:00:43.480
to allow you to
build apps that could

00:00:43.480 --> 00:00:45.760
be used for augmented reality.

00:00:45.760 --> 00:00:46.810
Get started now.

00:00:46.810 --> 00:00:48.410
